data.title: High School Musical 1 (2006)
data.meta_description: Oh it so old movie now.. I remember when it was hot news.. I didn't care much of this movie and all that sequels at first, but then I saw on youtube first time damn.. I liked it :D Even though I didn't understand everything but then it came on TV and we recorded it.…
data.text:
Oh it so old movie now.. I remember when it was hot news..

I didn’t care much of this movie and all that sequels at first, but then I saw on youtube first time damn.. I liked it 😀 Even though I didn’t understand everything but then it came on TV and we recorded it.

I like almost all song and whole movie. But I still like that movie, they all are so young and cute here. 😀 But typical thing is (it’s Disney what can I say) bad turns good at the end.. .and in next movie they are bad again..

Sharpay:”We need to save our show from people who don’t know the difference between a Tony Award and Tony Hawk.”

Mrs.Bolton:” Did we really fly all this way just to play more basketball?”

Jack ja Troy:”Yeah.”

Darbus:” Was that a cell phone?”

Kelsi:”No ma’am, that was the warning bell.”

Troy:” Uh-oh. I better…”

Chad:”No. You do NOT want to get into that man. Too much drama.”

Darbus:”Mr. Danforth! This is a place of learning, not a hockey arena.”

Chad:” Look, you’re a hoops dude. Not a musical singer person. Have you ever seen Michael Crawford on a cereal box?”

Troy:”Who’s Michael Crawford?”

Chad:”Exactly my point.”

Chad:” How can you expect the rest of us to be focused on a game when you’re off somewhere in leotards singing ‘Twinkle Town’…”

Troy:”No one said ANYTHING about leotards.”

Chad:”Not yet my friend, but just you wait.”

Sharpay:”We have to do something.”

Troy:” Whoa, don’t tell me you’re good at hoops too.”

Gabriella:”You know, I once scored 41 points on a league game.”

Troy:”No way.”

Gabriella:”Mmhmm. Yeah, and on the same day I invented the space shuttle and microwaved popcorn.”

Troy:”Ah, microwave popcorn. Haha, very funny.”

Skatedude 1:”If Troy can tell his secret, then I’m coming clean. I play the cello! ”

Skatedude 2: ” Awesome! What is it? A saw?”

Skaterdude 1:”No dude, it’s like a giant violin!”

Sharpay:”Someone’s gotta tell her the rules.”

Troy:”Excatly….And what’re the rules?”

Chad:”So, you’re coming with me to the after-party, right?”

Taylor:”As in, like, a date?”

Chad:”Must be your lucky day.”

Darbus:”That’ll be 15 minutes for you as well, Mr. Danforth. Count ’em! ”

Taylor:” That might be difficult for Chad, since he probably can’t count that high. ”

Jack Bolton:”Where’s my team, Darbus… What the heck are those two doing in a tree?”

Darbus:”It’s called crime and punishment, Bolton. Beside, proximity to the arts is cleansing for the soul.”

Jack:”Can we have a talk? Please? And you two, in the gym… now.”

Darbus:” This school is about more than just young men in baggy shorts flinging balls for touchdowns.”

Jack:”Baskets. Uh, they shoot baskets.”

Chad:”Hey, the whole team’s htting the gym for free period, what do you want us to run?”

Troy:”I can’t – I, uh, have to catch up on, uh, homework.”

Chad:”What? It’s only the second day back, even I’m not even behind on homework yet. And I’ve been behind on homework since preschool.”

Gabriella:”You’re a cool guy, Troy. But not for the reasons your friends think.”

Chad:” What spell has this elevated IQ temptress girl cast that suddenly makes you wanna be in a musical?”

Chad:” People are starting to do other stuff. Okay, stuff that’s not their stuff.”

Troy:” Now that’s impossible.”

Sharpay:”What’s impossible,Troy? I wouldn’t think “impossible” was in your vocabulary.”

Guy:”Hey, you know what? Someday you guys might thank me for this. Or Not.”

Jack:” You’re the playmaker… not a singer… right?”

Troy:”Did you ever think that maybe I could be both?”

Troy:”That’s travelling. No, that’s really bad travelling.”

10/8)
